The '''Roolek clan''' was a [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] clan on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Rodia/Legends|Rodia]]. 

==History==
The clan was decimated during the [[Rodian Clan Wars]] were they fought savagely against the [[Chattza clan/Legends|Chattza Clan]]; as a result, the Chattza [[Navik/Legends|Navik the Red]] ordered to exterminate them.<ref name="guide">''[[Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide]]''</ref> 

By the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], few clan members survived that genocide attempt and went into hiding on Rodia, keeping their identities secret, open only to their allied clans. Most of them escaped offworld, lest Navik sought them out such as he did with the [[Tetsu Clan]]; those would imemdiately attack against any Chattza clan member they would meet on another [[planet/Legends|planet]].<ref name="guide" /> A small groups of those that stayed behind, were hiding in [[Iskaayuma/Legends|Iskaayuma]], and the  [[Rodmark Weapons Plant/Legends|Rodmark Weapons Plant]] operated secretly as a stronghold.<ref name="Street Drama" />

The [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Inntak]] once hired a group of [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] to help capture any Rooleks that would attend the last show of the [[Rodian Galactic Drama Troupe]]'s tour. Three groups arrived on [[speeder/Legends|speeders]] to watch the show, ten beings in total; after its end, they returned to the factory, followed by the hunters.<ref name="Street Drama">{{WEGCite|story=Street Drama|book=Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide}}</ref>

